FORMER Orlando Pirates coach Milutin "Micho" Sredojevic's mother, Rada, has died. She was 70-years-old at the time of her death. The passing of the Zambia national team coach's mother was confirmed by the Football Association of Zambia (FAZ) on Sunday. "Chipolopolo coach Milutin "Micho" SredojevicÂ  has lost his mother Rada aged 70. FAZ president Andrew Kamanga and his executive committee with secretarial staff joins the football family in mourning with coach Micho." The former Uganda Cranes coach Micho also confirmed the news saying: "I have remained just with best memories of herself in my heart, mind and soul with the best ingredients being the values she engraved in me. My mother will forever be inside me and whatever i did in African football i owe it to her."